-{"id":"franken_numpy-k74v","title":"[REALITY-CHECK-EPIC] Close fnp_python passthrough gap for numpy.__all__ (~200 wrappers)","description":"Parent epic for the ~200 missing passthrough wrappers that would raise fnp_python's numpy.__all__ coverage from 43% to ~100%.\n\nScope: per-category child beads (P0/P1/P2/P3) covering 70 core ufuncs, 106 core functions, 21 classes, ~15 constants/indexing/version items. Excludes dtype scalars (50 items, Category 4) since those can be re-exported wholesale via a single registration sweep.\n\nStrategy: mirrors the established pattern in fnp-python/src/lib.rs (one #[pyfunction] delegating to numpy.<name>, registered in module init, listed in module_exports_python_surface smoke test, plus a dedicated <name>_matches_numpy_* parity oracle test). Each wrapper ~30-80 lines including tests.\n\nGating question (resolved by separate strategy-question bead): whether to structure as nested submodules (fnp_python.linalg.svd) or keep flat (linalg_svd).\n\nAudit artifact: audit_numpy_reality.md.\nVerification: cargo test -p fnp-python module_exports_python_surface must list every new name; full module_exports_python_surface still passes; new <name>_matches_numpy_* tests pass individually via rch.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:20:03.423927977Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T09:20:03.423927977Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"franken_numpy-k74v.1","title":"[REALITY-CHECK] Add 70 missing core numpy ufunc passthrough wrappers to fnp_python","description":"Parent: franken_numpy-k74v (REALITY-CHECK-EPIC).\n\nMissing ufunc names (from numpy.__all__ intersect numpy.ufunc, not present in fnp_python):\n  abs, absolute, acos, acosh, add, arccos, arccosh, arcsin, arcsinh, arctan, arctan2,\n  arctanh, asin, asinh, atan, atan2, atanh, bitwise_and, bitwise_count, bitwise_invert,\n  bitwise_left_shift, bitwise_not, bitwise_or, bitwise_right_shift, bitwise_xor, conj,\n  cos, cosh, divide, divmod, equal, exp, exp2, float_power, fmax, fmin, gcd, greater,\n  greater_equal, isnat, lcm, left_shift, less, less_equal, log, log10, log2,\n  logical_and, logical_not, logical_or, logical_xor, matmul, maximum, minimum, mod,\n  multiply, not_equal, power, remainder, right_shift, sin, sinh, sqrt, subtract,\n  tan, tanh, matrix_transpose (dup), vecmat, matvec\n\nPattern: one-line passthrough wrapper like existing square/cbrt/expm1/fabs/negative.\nEach follows:\n\n  #[pyfunction]\n  #[pyo3(signature = (x,))]       // or (x1, x2) for binary\n  fn <name>(py: Python<'_>, x: Py<PyAny>) -> PyResult<Py<PyAny>> {\n      let numpy = py.import(\"numpy\")?;\n      Ok(numpy.getattr(\"<name>\")?.call1((x.bind(py),))?.unbind())\n  }\n\nRegister in module init and module_exports_python_surface smoke test. Add one parity oracle test per family (trig, bitwise, comparison, etc.) rather than per-function to keep test count manageable.\n\nTrig (12): acos, acosh, arccos, arccosh, arcsin, arcsinh, arctan, arctanh, asin, asinh, atan, atanh (note asin/asinh etc. are Array-API aliases for arcsin/etc.)\nInverse-trig-binary (2): arctan2, atan2\nHyperbolic (4): cosh, sinh, tanh, (asinh/acosh/atanh already counted)\nArithmetic (10): add, subtract, multiply, divide, true_divide (dup), power, float_power, mod, remainder, divmod\nComparison (6): equal, not_equal, greater, greater_equal, less, less_equal\nLogical (4): logical_and, logical_not, logical_or, logical_xor\nBitwise (11): bitwise_and, bitwise_count, bitwise_invert, bitwise_left_shift, bitwise_not, bitwise_or, bitwise_right_shift, bitwise_xor, left_shift, right_shift, gcd, lcm\nExp/Log (6): exp, exp2, log, log10, log2, sqrt\nRounding/Elementary (4): abs, absolute, conj, isnat\nElementwise binary (4): fmax, fmin, maximum, minimum\nMatrix ops (3): matmul, matvec, vecmat\nTrig one-arg (3): sin, cos, tan\n\nPriority: P0-P1. These are the numpy API baseline — every tutorial uses np.add, np.sin, np.log, np.sqrt.\n\nVerification: rch exec -- cargo test -p fnp-python <family>_matches; cargo test -p fnp-python module_exports_python_surface.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:20:52.687278654Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T09:20:52.687278654Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-k74v.1","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-k74v","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:20:52.687278654Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
