 {"id":"franken_numpy-k74v.3","title":"[REALITY-CHECK] Add 21 numpy class passthroughs to fnp_python (errstate, finfo, iinfo, memmap, ...)","description":"Parent: franken_numpy-k74v.\n\nMissing numpy classes:\n  broadcast, busdaycalendar, dtype, errstate, finfo, flatiter, iinfo, int_, long,\n  matrix, memmap, ndarray, ndenumerate, ndindex, nditer, poly1d, recarray, record,\n  ufunc, uint, ulong\n\nPriority split:\n- P1 (practical passthroughs — trivial re-export):\n  errstate (context manager, common in numerical code)\n  finfo, iinfo (introspect float/int limits)\n  memmap (fnp-io has native support — can expose as fnp_python.memmap passthrough OR as a real pyclass wrapping fnp-io)\n  poly1d, matrix (legacy but still in tutorials)\n\n- P2 (design discussion required):\n  dtype, ndarray, nditer, ufunc, recarray, record\n  These would ideally be proper pyclass definitions backed by fnp_python types (not passthrough to numpy) — that's a significant architecture decision. For parity-oracle mode, a passthrough re-export (fnp_python.ndarray = numpy.ndarray) is acceptable.\n\n- P3 (rare / deprecated):\n  broadcast, busdaycalendar, flatiter, int_, long, ndenumerate, ndindex, uint, ulong\n\nVerification: getattr smoke test + type-name parity asserts.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:21:55.513533624Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:47:51.387442185Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:47:51.385611439Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — 19 numpy class names (broadcast, busdaycalendar, dtype, errstate, finfo, flatiter, iinfo, int_, long, matrix, memmap, ndarray, ndenumerate, ndindex, nditer, poly1d, recarray, record, ufunc) re-exported from fnp_python via numpy passthrough in commit 9db252a. Disjoint from k74v.4's dtype scalar set (uint, ulong live there, not here). Parity test module_reexports_numpy_class_types_matching_numpy asserts identity for 17 universal types + version-symmetric handling for int_/long. rch test: 5/5 passed. Future pyclass-native replacement (ndarray, dtype, ufunc) deferred to a separate architecture bead; passthrough is acceptable for parity-oracle mode per the bead spec.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-k74v.3","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-k74v","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:21:55.513533624Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-k74v.4","title":"[REALITY-CHECK] Re-export 50 numpy dtype scalar types from fnp_python","description":"Parent: franken_numpy-k74v.\n\nMissing dtype scalar types:\n  bool, bool_, byte, bytes_, cdouble, character, clongdouble, complex128, complex256,\n  complex64, complexfloating, csingle, datetime64, double, flexible, float128, float16,\n  float32, float64, floating, generic, half, inexact, int16, int32, int64, int8, intc,\n  integer, intp, longdouble, longlong, number, object_, short, signedinteger, single,\n  str_, timedelta64, ubyte, uint, uint16, uint32, uint64, uint8, uintc, uintp, ulong,\n  ulonglong, ushort, unsignedinteger, void\n\nThese are NumPy scalar types, typically used as dtype= arguments. A single module-init sweep can re-export all of them:\n\n  for name in [\"int8\", \"int16\", ...] { m.add(name, numpy.getattr(name)?)?; }\n\nImplementation: ~15 lines of Rust in fnp_python(m) module init, iterating a const array of names.\n\nVerification: assert_eq!(fnp_python.getattr(\"int8\"), numpy.getattr(\"int8\")) smoke tests for each; one parametric test is sufficient.\n\nPriority P2: users can currently pass numpy.int8 directly to fnp_python wrappers (dtype: Py<PyAny>), so this is cosmetic but important for the 'full API' claim.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:22:09.470074161Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T11:44:24.199950637Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T11:44:24.198099285Z","close_reason":"Closed by cc-numpy — 52 numpy dtype scalar names (bool, bool_, byte, bytes_, cdouble, character, clongdouble, complex64/128/256, complexfloating, csingle, datetime64, double, flexible, float16/32/64/128, floating, generic, half, inexact, int8/16/32/64, intc, integer, intp, longdouble, longlong, number, object_, short, signedinteger, single, str_, timedelta64, ubyte, uint, uint8/16/32/64, uintc, uintp, ulong, ulonglong, ushort, unsignedinteger, void) re-exported from fnp_python via numpy passthrough in commit daebe80. Parity test module_reexports_numpy_dtype_scalar_types_matching_numpy asserts identity (ours.is(&theirs)) for 50 universal types and platform-symmetric handling for complex256/float128/bool. rch test: 4/4 passed. Platform-missing types skipped gracefully.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-k74v.4","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-k74v","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:22:09.470074161Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"franken_numpy-k74v.5","title":"[REALITY-CHECK] Decide fnp_python submodule namespace strategy","description":"Parent: franken_numpy-k74v. Blocks per-category implementation beads.\n\nProblem: fnp_python currently exposes numpy submodule content FLAT:\n  fnp_python.linalg_svd       (vs numpy.linalg.svd)\n  fnp_python.ma_argmax        (vs numpy.ma.argmax)\n  fnp_python.testing_assert_allclose  (vs numpy.testing.assert_allclose)\n  fnp_python.recfunctions_drop_fields (vs numpy.lib.recfunctions.drop_fields)\n\nThe README claims 'full API, edge cases and all'. Under flat namespace, a user doing:\n  import fnp_python as np\n  np.linalg.svd(...)\nFAILS — must write np.linalg_svd(...).\n\nOptions:\n  (A) Add real nested submodules via pyo3 PyModule::new(py, \"linalg\"). Requires restructuring lib.rs into submodule registration blocks plus duplicating wrappers (or re-registering them under nested modules). ~medium effort.\n  (B) Keep flat; add fnp_python.linalg = types.SimpleNamespace(svd=fnp_python.linalg_svd, ...) in a Python-side __init__ or a module attribute constructed at init. Cheap but requires users to  and this depends on how the module is imported.\n  (C) Keep flat and document in README that fnp_python uses flat namespace. Honest but breaks the 'drop-in' promise.\n\nRecommendation: (A) is closest to vision; (B) is pragmatic; (C) is the honest pivot.\n\nDecision required before implementation epic children can start. Currently blocks Category 5 (16 submodules) and also changes the shape of ufunc/function/class wrappers (should they register under fnp_python.<submodule>.<name>?).\n\nVerification on resolution:\n  python -c 'import fnp_python as np; np.linalg.svd(np.eye(3))' must succeed\n  python -c 'import fnp_python.linalg' must succeed if real-submodule route chosen","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"question","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:22:23.641419177Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-23T18:00:10.489122329Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T18:00:10.486617578Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"franken_numpy-k74v.5","depends_on_id":"franken_numpy-k74v","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-04-22T09:22:23.641419177Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
